<VSCode.Cell language="markdown">
# 00. Load LANL Earthquake Prediction Dataset

This notebook loads the Kaggle LANL Earthquake Prediction training data from `data/train.csv`.

The dataset contains:
- `acoustic_data`
- `time_to_failure`

For this baseline, `acoustic_data` is used as a proxy for shear stress.
This is an engineering baseline, not a claim of exact physical equivalence.

Dataset link:
https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/LANL-Earthquake-Prediction/overview
</VSCode.Cell>
<VSCode.Cell language="python">
import sys
from pathlib import Path
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

sys.path.insert(0, str(Path.cwd().parent))
from src import io

train_path = Path('data/train.csv')
print(f'Using LANL dataset path: {train_path.resolve()}')
if not train_path.exists():
    raise FileNotFoundError(
        'Expected LANL dataset at data/train.csv. Please place the Kaggle LANL train.csv file there.'
    )

lanl_df = io.load_lanl_train(str(train_path), nrows=None)
print(f'Loaded LANL data shape: {lanl_df.shape}')
print(lanl_df.head())
</VSCode.Cell>
<VSCode.Cell language="python">
summary = io.describe_dataset(lanl_df)
print('Dataset schema summary:')
for key, value in summary.items():
    print(f'  {key}: {value}')
</VSCode.Cell>
<VSCode.Cell language="python">
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 1, figsize=(14, 8), sharex=True)
axes[0].plot(lanl_df['time'], lanl_df['acoustic_data'], color='tab:blue', linewidth=0.5)
axes[0].set_ylabel('acoustic_data (proxy)')
axes[0].set_title('LANL acoustic_data signal')
axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

axes[1].plot(lanl_df['time'], lanl_df['time_to_failure'], color='tab:red', linewidth=0.8)
axes[1].set_ylabel('time_to_failure')
axes[1].set_xlabel('sample index (time)')
axes[1].set_title('LANL time_to_failure signal')
axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
</VSCode.Cell>
<VSCode.Cell language="python">
cleaned_path = Path('data/lanl_train_cleaned.csv')
lanl_df.to_csv(cleaned_path, index=False)
print(f'Cleaned LANL dataset saved to: {cleaned_path.resolve()}')
</VSCode.Cell>
